# Setting up Airflow with three containers with postgres db backend
First start the postgres service, then use the "find ip address" command to get the database IP. Then add this
ip to the airflow.cfg on the webserver, before running `airflow db init`

# Create user for webserver
To create an user with "Admin" role and username equals to "admin", run:

```
airflow users create \
      --username admin \
      --firstname FIRST_NAME \
      --lastname LAST_NAME \
      --role Admin \
      --email admin@example.org
```

# Start the airflow service using docker compose
`docker compose up postgres`
`docker compose up initdb`
`docker compose up webserver scheduler`

# Find ip address of docker container
`docker inspect -f '{{range.NetworkSettings.Networks}}{{.IPAddress}}{{end}}' <container_name_or_id>`